title: Visit Union Branch
new-page: true
is-card: true
tags: day_affairs
view-if: union_visit_daily_timer = 0
on-arrival: day_actions += 1; union_visit_timer = 1

Visit a local union branch to strengthen ties with organized labor and show the ALP flag. Our presence can help counter communist organizing efforts.

Which state's union movement should we visit?

- @nsw: New South Wales
- @vic: Victoria
- @qld: Queensland
- @sa: South Australia
- @wa: Western Australia
- @tas: Tasmania
- @no_visit: Cancel visit

@nsw
on-arrival: {!
// Small chance to reduce communist influence
if (Math.random() < 0.3) {
    Q.nsw_workers_cpa *= 0.99;
    Q.nsw_actu_communist -= 0.01;
}
// Strengthen Right NSW and Union Right
Q.right_alp_nsw_strength += 0.3;
Q.right_alp_union_strength += 0.4;
// Small Grouper benefit
Q.groupers_strength += 0.1;
!}

We visited a union branch in Sydney's industrial heartland. The NSW Right's union networks ensure we're well-received.

[? if nsw_workers_cpa < nsw_workers_cpa + 0.01 : Our presence helped counter some communist agitation among the rank-and-file. ?]

The union officials appreciate Labor's solidarity and remind us of upcoming wage claims.

@vic
on-arrival: {!
// Higher chance for communist encounter in Victoria
let communist_present = Math.random() < 0.4;
if (communist_present) {
    Q.vic_workers_cpa *= 0.985;
    Q.vic_actu_communist -= 0.015;
    Q.groupers_strength += 0.5; // Groupers benefit more from anti-communist work
    Q.left_vic_dissent += 2; // Left doesn't like this approach
}
// Strengthen Groupers and Union Right
Q.groupers_strength += 0.3;
Q.right_alp_union_strength += 0.2;
Q.right_alp_south_strength += 0.1;
!}

We attended a branch meeting in Melbourne. The atmosphere is tense - communist influence runs deep in some Victorian unions.

[? if communist_present : The Groupers seized the moment, challenging communist sympathizers in a heated debate. The Left faction privately grumbles about our 'red-baiting.' ?]
[? if not communist_present : Union officials welcomed our visit, though the factional undercurrents are never far from the surface. ?]

@qld
on-arrival: {!
