@wa
on-arrival: {!
// Moderate-high communist presence (wharfies, miners)
if (Math.random() < 0.4) {
    Q.wa_workers_cpa *= 0.985;
    Q.wa_actu_communist -= 0.015;
    Q.left_nsw_dissent += 1; // Left doesn't like anti-red activity
}
// Mixed factional benefit - WA is complicated
Q.right_alp_union_strength += 0.4;
Q.groupers_strength += 0.2;
Q.left_nsw_strength += 0.1; // Even Left benefits from union ties
!}

We visited Perth or Fremantle. WA's isolation creates unique dynamics - communist influence is strong in the wharfies and miners, but so is Labor solidarity.

[? if wa_workers_cpa < wa_workers_cpa + 0.015 : We made inroads against communist organizing, though it's an uphill battle in the maritime unions. ?]

Distance from the eastern states makes WA Labor more independent and pragmatic.

